VITE_SITE_DESCRIPTION="Hi! Welcome to my little corner of the internet! I am a 2nd-year CS student at the University of Waterloo. Currently, I am a research intern at Huawei Noah's Ark Lab working on efficient spatial foundation models, as well as a research assistant at the UW Multicore Lab working on concurrent data structures on GPUs. Before this, I spent two years working at Wolfram Research as a student researcher. I built various fun projects ranging from Lambda Calculus operator construction to applications and low-level acceleration of Cellular Automata. Since January 2026, I have been a committee member of the Canadian Computing Competition, Canada's largest programming contest for IOI selection. I authored CCO 2026 Day 1 Problem 3, which was the hardest problem that year. I go to a lot of hackathons, including TreeHacks, CalHacks, and NexHacks. Reach out to me if you want to team up!"
